<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40035e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40035e">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40035e"> 35(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> under God / catechumanate</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">They are now Christians. The kind of Christians they are is almost entirely due, under God, to the teacher who taught them during their catechumenate, and to him who is now shepherding them. In connexion with mass movements there is no more vitally important person than the &ldquo;village teacher.&rdquo; He is the pin of the wheel. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI1"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 71</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Catechumen = a person under instruction in the rudiments of Christianity, as in the early church; a neophyte. </mm> </dd></dl>
